cs.NA, cs.MS, cs.CE, cs.DS, cs.SC

Reasoning: 

- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis): The paper focuses on accelerating the H-matrix vector multiplication in a boundary element method (BEM) analysis, which involves numerical computations. 
- cs.MS (Mathematical Software): The paper proposes three methods to introduce mixed precision computing to H-matrix vector multiplication, which can be considered as a software development effort. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science): The paper applies the H-matrix approximation technique to a practical problem in computational engineering (BEM analysis). 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The H-matrix approximation technique involves splitting a target dense matrix into multiple submatrices, which can be seen as a data structure. 
- cs.SC (Symbolic Computation and Formal Verification): This category is less likely, but the paper does involve some mathematical analysis and verification of the proposed methods.
